### Competitive intelligence inputs (Agent 101)

**Purpose:** Ensure slide content matches **structured** competitive intelligence (matrices, E2E CI briefs, gap reports), not only high-level PMF narrative from **120**.

**Paths to read when present and in scope** (use `read_file` / repo paths before drafting `slides_spec.json`):

| Artifact | Path pattern | When to use |
|----------|--------------|-------------|
| Global matrix | `research/competitive/matrices/global-competitive-matrix.md` | Enterprise ATS / global competitive decks |
| Regional matrix | `research/competitive/matrices/{uk,fr,de,au,jp,in,ca,gcc}-competitive-matrix.md` | Match **region** to topic (UK, France, Germany, Australia, Japan, India, Canada, GCC) |
| GCC E2E CI brief | `research/competitive/gcc/e2e-ci-brief-[feature-slug]-[YYYY-MM-DD].md` | After **GCC E2E** Step 5 (**101**); or when user names the brief |
| Point-in-time scans | `research/competitive/[region]/[competitor]-[date].md` | Deep-dive competitor slides, battle cards |

**When to apply this section**

- User asks for **competitive**, **parity**, **battle card**, **regional** recruiting landscape, **GCC** (or other listed regions), **PMF** readout that includes competitors, **roadmap** positioning vs vendors, or mentions **101**, **CI brief**, **competitive matrix**, **GCC e2e**, or post-**101** deck refresh.

**Content rules**

- Prefer **Native / Workaround / True gap** wording and citations from **101** outputs over unsourced competitor marketing.
- For **CI-heavy** decks, add **at least 1–3** dedicated slides after agenda, for example:
  - **Competitive snapshot** – top 3 regional or global players + one-line positioning each (from matrix executive summary / profiles).
  - **Workday parity summary** – compact table or bullets from matrix **Workday Competitive Response** or E2E brief parity table.
  - **Implications / watch list** – true gaps, RICE callouts, or roadmap hooks **only if** present in source (do not invent).
- **Speaker notes (mandatory):** Include **References** with URLs from the matrix/brief **Sources** sections and note file paths (e.g. `research/competitive/matrices/gcc-competitive-matrix.md`) so presenters can trace claims.

**British English** on slide body text per **`010-style-guide.mdc`** where applicable.

### Competitive intelligence readout

**Purpose:** Stakeholder deck summarising **101** outputs (matrices, briefs, scans) for sales, exec, or PM review.

**Structure:**

1. TITLE – deck title + date / region
2. Auto-agenda
3. Title Only – **Method and sources** (which matrix/brief/scan files were used; one line each)
4. Section Title – **Landscape**
5. Title Only_Alt – **Regional or global competitive snapshot** (key players, 3–5 bullets)
6. Title Only – **Parity and gaps** (table or bullets: Native / Workaround / True gap for initiative-relevant capabilities)
7. Section Title – **Implications**
8. Title Only_Alt – **Implications for Workday Recruiting** (from matrix roadmap / gap summary if present)
9. 1/2 Headline_Alt – **Key takeaway**
10. Title Only – **Next steps** (e.g. refresh matrix quarterly, link to PRD)
11. Bumper Slide

Use **speaker_notes** on every content slide with **References** pointing to matrix/brief URLs and file paths.

